  "body": "Say I have the following folder structure:\r\n\r\n```\r\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ tsconfig.json\r\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ package.json\r\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ packages\r\n  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ contracts\r\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ buidler.config.ts\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf I run `yarn buidler compile` within the \"contracts\" folder, the `buidler.config.ts` file is not picked up and I'm given the welcome message:\r\n\r\n> üë∑ Welcome to Buidler v1.3.4 üë∑‚Äç‚Äç\r\n\r\nI suppose that the issue is Buidler not looking for the `tsconfig.json` file a few levels up the folder path. I know that this is an edge case, but I opened the issue anyways, in case it turns out there's more people like me who'd like to use Buidler in a monorepo.",
